
[1]determination

   DETERMINATION, n.

   1. The act of determining or deciding.

   2. Decision of a question in the mind; firm resolution; settled
   purpose; as, they have acquainted me with their determination.

   3. Judicial decision; the ending of a controversy or suit by the
   judgment of a court. Justice is promoted by a speedy determination of
   causes, civil and criminal.

   4. Absolute direction to a certain end.

   Remissness can by no means consist with a constant determination of the
   will to the greatest apparent good.

   5. An ending; a putting an end to; as the determination of a will.
